verses.text_plain: Call now, if there be any that will answer thee; and to which of the saints wilt thou turn?
verses.verse_html:
1Call now, if there be any that will answer thee; and to which of the saints wilt thou turn? ▼
▼ turn: or, look?

tokens.text: thee; and to which of the saints

verses.text_plain: For wrath killeth the foolish man, and envy slayeth the silly one.
verses.verse_html:
2For wrath killeth the foolish man, and envy slayeth the silly one. ▼
▼ envy: or, indignation

verses.text_plain: I have seen the foolish taking root: but suddenly I cursed his habitation.
verses.verse_html: 3I have seen the foolish taking root: but suddenly I cursed his habitation.

verses.text_plain: His children are far from safety, and they are crushed in the gate, neither is there any to deliver them.
verses.verse_html: 4His children are far from safety, and they are crushed in the gate, neither is there any to deliver them.

verses.text_plain: Whose harvest the hungry eateth up, and taketh it even out of the thorns, and the robber swalloweth up their substance.
verses.verse_html: 5Whose harvest the hungry eateth up, and taketh it even out of the thorns, and the robber swalloweth up their substance.

verses.text_plain: Although affliction cometh not forth of the dust, neither doth trouble spring out of the ground;
verses.verse_html:
6Although affliction cometh not forth of the dust, neither doth trouble spring out of the ground; ▼
▼ affliction: or, iniquity

verses.text_plain: Yet man is born unto trouble, as the sparks fly upward.
verses.verse_html:
7Yet man is born unto trouble, as the sparks fly upward. ▼
▼ trouble: or, labour
 , ▼
▼ sparks…: Heb. the sons of the burning coal lift up to fly

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sparks…: Heb. the sons of the burning coal lift up to fly
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sparks…: Heb. the sons of the burning coal lift up to fly

verses.text_plain: I would seek unto God, and unto God would I commit my cause:
verses.verse_html: 8I would seek unto God, and unto God would I commit my cause:

verses.text_plain: Which doeth great things and unsearchable; marvellous things without number:
verses.verse_html:
9Which doeth great things and unsearchable; marvellous things without number: ▼
▼ unsearchable: Heb. there is no search
 , ▼
▼ without…: Heb. till there be no number

footnotes.body_text: ▼ unsearchable: Heb. there is no search
footnotes.body_html: ▼ unsearchable: Heb. there is no search

footnotes.body_text: ▼ without…: Heb. till there be no number
footnotes.body_html: ▼ without…: Heb. till there be no number

verses.text_plain: Who giveth rain upon the earth, and sendeth waters upon the fields:
verses.verse_html:
10Who giveth rain upon the earth, and sendeth waters upon the fields: ▼
▼ fields: Heb. outplaces

verses.text_plain: To set up on high those that be low; that those which mourn may be exalted to safety.
verses.verse_html: 11To set up on high those that be low; that those which mourn may be exalted to safety.

verses.text_plain: He disappointeth the devices of the crafty, so that their hands cannot perform their enterprise.
verses.verse_html:
12He disappointeth the devices of the crafty, so that their hands cannot perform their enterprise. ▼
▼ their enterprise: or, any thing

footnotes.body_html: ▼ their enterprise: or, any thing

verses.text_plain: He taketh the wise in their own craftiness: and the counsel of the froward is carried headlong.
verses.verse_html: 13He taketh the wise in their own craftiness: and the counsel of the froward is carried headlong.

verses.text_plain: They meet with darkness in the daytime, and grope in the noonday as in the night.
verses.verse_html:
14They meet with darkness in the daytime, and grope in the noonday as in the night. ▼
▼ meet…: or, run into

footnotes.body_html: ▼ meet…: or, run into

verses.text_plain: But he saveth the poor from the sword, from their mouth, and from the hand of the mighty.
verses.verse_html: 15But he saveth the poor from the sword, from their mouth, and from the hand of the mighty.

verses.text_plain: So the poor hath hope, and iniquity stoppeth her mouth.
verses.verse_html: 16So the poor hath hope, and iniquity stoppeth her mouth.

verses.text_plain: Behold, happy is the man whom God correcteth: therefore despise not thou the chastening of the Almighty:
verses.verse_html: 17Behold, happy is the man whom God correcteth: therefore despise not thou the chastening of the Almighty:

verses.text_plain: For he maketh sore, and bindeth up: he woundeth, and his hands make whole.
verses.verse_html: 18For he maketh sore, and bindeth up: he woundeth, and his hands make whole.

verses.text_plain: He shall deliver thee in six troubles: yea, in seven there shall no evil touch thee.
verses.verse_html: 19He shall deliver thee in six troubles: yea, in seven there shall no evil touch thee.

verses.text_plain: In famine he shall redeem thee from death: and in war from the power of the sword.
verses.verse_html:
20In famine he shall redeem thee from death: and in war from the power of the sword. ▼
▼ power: Heb. hands

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt be hid from the scourge of the tongue: neither shalt thou be afraid of destruction when it cometh.
verses.verse_html:
21Thou shalt be hid from the scourge of the tongue: neither shalt thou be afraid of destruction when it cometh. ▼
▼ from…: or, when the tongue scourgeth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ from…: or, when the tongue scourgeth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ from…: or, when the tongue scourgeth

verses.text_plain: At destruction and famine thou shalt laugh: neither shalt thou be afraid of the beasts of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 22At destruction and famine thou shalt laugh: neither shalt thou be afraid of the beasts of the earth.

verses.text_plain: For thou shalt be in league with the stones of the field: and the beasts of the field shall be at peace with thee.
verses.verse_html: 23For thou shalt be in league with the stones of the field: and the beasts of the field shall be at peace with thee.

tokens.text: For thou shalt be in league

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt know that thy tabernacle shall be in peace; and thou shalt visit thy habitation, and shalt not sin.
verses.verse_html:
24And thou shalt know that thy tabernacle shall be in peace; and thou shalt visit thy habitation, and shalt not sin. ▼
▼ thy tabernacle…: or, peace is thy tabernacle
 , ▼
▼ sin: or, err

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy tabernacle…: or, peace is thy tabernacle
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy tabernacle…: or, peace is thy tabernacle

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt know also that thy seed shall be great, and thine offspring as the grass of the earth.
verses.verse_html:
25Thou shalt know also that thy seed shall be great, and thine offspring as the grass of the earth. ▼
▼ great: or, much

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt come to thy grave in a full age, like as a shock of corn cometh in in his season.
verses.verse_html:
26Thou shalt come to thy grave in a full age, like as a shock of corn cometh in in his season. ▼
▼ cometh in: Heb. ascendeth

tokens.text: like as a shock of corn

footnotes.body_html: ▼ cometh in: Heb. ascendeth

verses.text_plain: Lo this, we have searched it, so it is; hear it, and know thou it for thy good.
verses.verse_html:
27Lo this, we have searched it, so it is; hear it, and know thou it for thy good. ▼
▼ for…: Heb. for thyself

footnotes.body_html: ▼ for…: Heb. for thyself
